PROMPT equal_temperament_analysis
WITH BUDGET 6000 tokens
USING MODEL "claude-sonnet-4-5"

SELECT
    system_role("You are a music theory and acoustics expert specializing in historical tuning systems, temperament theory, and the mathematical foundations of musical intervals with deep knowledge of how different tuning systems affect harmonic purity and key usability.")

GENERATE
    analyze_temperament("Explain equal temperament in detail, covering: the definition of equal temperament as a tuning system that divides the octave into 12 equal semitones, each separated by exactly 100 cents or a frequency ratio of 2^(1/12), how this mathematical precision allows every key to sound equally in tune or equally out of tune, the compromise nature of equal temperament where all intervals except the octave are slightly detuned from their pure mathematical ratios, specific examples of how the equal-tempered fifth (700 cents) is 2 cents flat compared to the pure fifth (701.955 cents) and the major third (400 cents) is 13.7 cents sharp compared to the pure major third (386.3 cents), what equal temperament replaced including meantone temperament which made thirds very pure but created severely out-of-tune fifths in remote keys like G# major, just intonation which provided perfectly pure intervals in one key but became increasingly dissonant as music moved to related keys, and Pythagorean tuning which gave pure fifths and fourths but made thirds sound harsh, the historical development showing how keyboard instruments before equal temperament were limited to playing in only a few keys without offensive dissonance, how composers like Bach demonstrated the viability of equal temperament through works like The Well-Tempered Clavier, the practical benefits including the ability to transpose music to any key, modulate freely between distant keys, and use the full chromatic spectrum without retuning instruments, why it became the universal standard for fixed-pitch instruments like pianos despite the slight impurity of all intervals, and how this compromise enabled the harmonic complexity and key relationships that characterize Classical and Romantic music.")
WITH OUTPUT BUDGET 2500 tokens, TEMPERATURE 0.2, FORMAT markdown;